<p>Game of Thrones: Rise of the Hightower is a tale of ambition, intrigue, and power, exploring the consequences of a divided Westeros and the lengths one ruler will go to in order to bring a shattered realm back to its former glory. Like its predecessor, the series will draw upon historical references and expertly weave them into a richly-textured, fantastical world, while also deconstructing the perceived victories and resolutions from the end of Season 8, ensuring that this new chapter in the Game of Thrones saga is as gripping as the original.</p></div>

